New spot that makes the competition in the area for Mexican even stronger. I had to try the Pambozo, which I haven't seen offered in any other Mexican joints. It's similar to a torta, but has a soft seasoned bread instead. The horchata was also delightful.

While this neighborhood is being built up with multi-million dollar projects and fancy restaurants, it's nice to stop by a legit Logan Square family-owned joint once in awhile.  The owner (Enrique) is passionate about food, and especially bringing Mexico City street food to Chicago.  The Pambozo, which will probably be a carb-overload for some, is definitely an experience if you like bread so spicy it's red.  The Horchata isn't too sweet, making it my favorite in the city.
